Defendant Kevin J Mendieta Ramirez in court with attorney Matt Last.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter Vicki Bermudez appeared in person.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #9:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 6 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT;
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*Perform 100 Hours community service. 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done. 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be refunded to poster);

CONDITION TIME: 6 MONTHS, non working hours with standard release conditions.  Defendant remanded into custody and sentence to commence forthwith.   (apply 42 days credit).

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new law violations.
